The paper deals with the concept of utility in economics and proposes an approach for efficient utility mining on time-ordered sequence data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of databases (cs.DB) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The proposed approach also involves the use of machine learning techniques such as projection and pruning, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also discusses the insights and information derived from the high-utility sequential patterns, which suggests a possible connection to information retrieval (cs.IR).
